<div class="postright">
<h3>Simple BASH Prompt for Parrot 3.5</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<p>Hi Community,</p><p>I like Parrot O/S very much and dig the funky default BASH prompt however in the interests of minimisation, I offer my simple BASH prompt.</p><p>From my ~/.bashrc</p><p>PS1=&#039;${debian_chroot:+($debian_chroot)}\[\033[01;32m\]\u\[\033[00m\]\[\033[01;34m\] \w\[\033[00m\]\[\033[01;33m\] &gt;&gt;\[\033[00m\] &#039;</p><p>This results in a Bold Green Username, Bold Blue short Filepath and a Yellow &gt;&gt; $PROMPT</p><p>Hack as you see fit 8-)</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="inbox">
